{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: diagnostic-report-lab-eu_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH DiagnosticReport instance conforming to the
    DiagnosticReportLabEu profile (EU Laboratory Report). This resource
    acts as the aggregating document-level record that ties together the
    patient, specimens, and individual Observation results of a laboratory
    report.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: DiagnosticReportLabEu
    Fixed elements:
      category[studyType] = $loinc#26436-6 "Laboratory studies (set)"
      code                = $loinc#11502-2 "Laboratory report"
      status              = #registered

  NO HTML OUTPUT
    This template produces no HTML table rows. Both %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%%
    sections use explicit `<!-- empty -->` HTML comment markers rather than
    `emitHEAD()` / `emitHTML()` calls. The FSH narrative is set to
    `text.status = #empty` (intentionally absent narrative).

  TWO IDENTIFIER SLICES — BOTH UNDER HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID
    Two separate identifier slices are emitted, both using the same OID
    namespace (`HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID`) but carrying different values:
      Slice 1 — `composition.identifier`: the identifier of the associated
                Composition document.
      Slice 2 — `diagnosticreport.identifier`: the DiagnosticReport's own
                business identifier.
    This pairing ensures the DiagnosticReport is cross-referenceable with
    both the Composition it accompanies and its own record system.

  R5 BACK-PORT EXTENSION — DiagnosticReportCompositionR5
    FHIR R4 DiagnosticReport does not natively include a `composition`
    element. A named back-port extension slice is used to carry this link:
      * extension[DiagnosticReportCompositionR5].valueReference =
          Reference(urn:uuid:{{ composition.instanceid }})
    The bracket notation `[DiagnosticReportCompositionR5]` addresses a named
    extension slice defined in the DiagnosticReportLabEu profile. This is
    not a plain `extension[+]` append — the slice name must match the profile
    definition exactly.

  STATUS — #registered
    The report status is hardcoded as `#registered` (report exists but
    results are not yet finalised). This may be appropriate for the synthetic
    pipeline's generation stage. Consider whether `#final` would be more
    appropriate for completed synthetic reports.

  SPECIMEN AND RESULT REFERENCES — LOOP PATTERNS
    specimenids — array of UUID strings; each produces one specimen[+] Reference.
    results     — array of objects each with an `.instanceid` field; each
                  produces one result[+] Reference. Note the difference:
                    specimenid is a plain UUID string ({{ s }})
                    result is an object accessed via {{ r.instanceid }}

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                       │ Type     │ Description                                │
  ├────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ diagnosticreport.instanceid    │ string   │ UUID for the DiagnosticReport resource.    │
  │ diagnosticreport.identifier    │ string   │ Business identifier value for the report   │
  │                                │          │ (identifier slice 2).                      │
  │ composition.instanceid         │ string   │ UUID of the associated Composition; used   │
  │                                │          │ in the R5 back-port extension Reference.   │
  │ composition.identifier         │ string   │ Composition business identifier value      │
  │                                │          │ (identifier slice 1).                      │
  │ patient.instanceid             │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.              │
  │ patient.name                   │ string   │ Full display name for the subject Reference.│
  │ specimenids                    │ string[] │ Array of Specimen resource UUIDs. One      │
  │                                │          │ specimen[+] Reference per entry.           │
  │ results                        │ object[] │ Array of Observation result objects. One   │
  │                                │          │ result[+] Reference per entry.             │
  │   [n].instanceid               │ string   │   UUID of the Observation resource.        │
  └────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for both identifier system URIs.

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $loinc — LOINC#26436-6 "Laboratory studies (set)" (category)
           — LOINC#11502-2 "Laboratory report" (code)

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-14
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-DiagnosticReport-" ~ diagnosticreport.instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: DiagnosticReportLabEu
Title: "Diagnostic Report"
Description: "Diagnostic Report"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ diagnosticreport.instanceid }}"

{#
  ── Two identifier slices — both under HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID OID ─────────────
  Slice 1: Composition identifier — cross-references the accompanying document.
  Slice 2: DiagnosticReport's own business identifier.
  Both share the same OID namespace; different values distinguish them.
#}
* identifier[+].system = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier[=].value = "{{ composition.identifier }}"
* identifier[=].assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

* identifier[+].system = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier[=].value = "{{ diagnosticreport.identifier }}"
* identifier[=].assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

{#
  ── R5 back-port extension — links DiagnosticReport to its Composition ───────
  FHIR R4 DiagnosticReport lacks a native composition element. The
  DiagnosticReportLabEu profile defines a named extension slice
  [DiagnosticReportCompositionR5] for this purpose. The bracket notation
  addresses the named slice — this is not a plain extension[+] append.
#}
* extension[DiagnosticReportCompositionR5].valueReference = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ composition.instanceid }})

{#
  ── Fixed status and categorisation ─────────────────────────────────────────
  status #registered indicates the report exists but is not yet finalised.
  category[studyType] and code are fixed LOINC codes required by the profile.
#}
* status = #registered
* category[studyType] = $loinc#26436-6 "Laboratory studies (set)"
* code = $loinc#11502-2 "Laboratory report"

{#
  ── Patient reference ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  ── Specimen references — plain UUID array ───────────────────────────────────
  specimenids contains UUID strings directly (not objects). Each entry
  is referenced as {{ s }} (no .instanceid property access).
#}
{% for s in specimenids %}
* specimen[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ s }})
{% endfor %}

{#
  ── Result references — object array ────────────────────────────────────────
  results contains objects with an .instanceid property (unlike specimenids).
  Each entry is referenced as {{ r.instanceid }}.
#}
{% for r in results %}
* result[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ r.instanceid }})
{% endfor %}

{#
  ── Intentionally empty narrative ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  The DiagnosticReport aggregates information from its referenced resources;
  no standalone human-readable narrative is meaningful here.
  text.status = #empty is the correct FHIR status for this case.
#}
* text.status = #empty
* text.div = "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">intentionally left empty / not meaningful</div>"

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
<!-- empty -->

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
<!-- empty -->
